{{Infobox person | name = Alberto Castagna | image = | imagesize = 150px | caption = | birth_name = Alberto Castagna | birth_date = {{birth date|1945|12|23}} | birth_place = [[Castiglion Fiorentino]], [[Italy]] | death_date = {{death date and age|2005|3|1|1945|12|23}} | death_place = [[Rome]], [[Italy]] | occupation = [[Television presenter|TV host]], journalist | years_active = 1982–2005 | nationality = [[Italy|Italian]] | spouse = Maria Concetta Romano (1994–1995) | partner = [[Francesca Rettondini]] (1995-2000) | children = Carolina (born 1992) }} '''Alberto Castagna''' (December 23, 1945 – March 1, 2005) was an [[Italy|Italian]] television host and journalist.
==Biography== Alberto Castagna started working as a journalist for the newspapers ''[[Il Piccolo]]'' and ''Settimanale''. In 1982, he debuted on TV in the [[Rai 2]] news program [[TG2]], initially as a reporter and then as a correspondent. In 1988, he collaborated with [[Pippo Baudo]] for one edition of the primetime show ''Serata d'onore''<ref name = RF>{{Cite news|author=Renato Franco|url=http://archiviostorico.corriere.it/2005/marzo/02/Stranamore_della_che_conquisto_Italia_co_9_050302119.shtml|title=Lo Stranamore della tv che conquistò l'Italia|work=Corriere della Sera|location=Italy|date=2 March 2005|page=41|accessdate=25 January 2011|cid=|language=it}}</ref> and then hosted the morning shows ''Mattina 2'' and, in 1992, ''I fatti vostri'', both directed by Michele Guardì.<ref>{{Cite news|author=|url=http://archiviostorico.corriere.it/1992/febbraio/24/oggi_fatti_vostri_con_Castagna_co_0_92022413646.shtml|title=Oggi "I fatti vostri" con Castagna|work=Corriere della Sera|location=Italy|date=1992-02-24|page=36|accessdate=25 January 2011|cid=|language=it}}</ref>
After winning a [[Telegatto]] as "personaggio maschile dell'anno", in 1993 he left [[RAI]] network switching to [[Fininvest]], where he hosted the afternoon quiz ''Sarà vero?'', aired by [[Canale 5]].<ref name = RF /> In 1994 he started hosting the primetime show ''Stranamore'', one of the most important TV shows in the 1990s,<ref name = RF /> the talk show ''Complotto di famiglia''<ref name = MI>{{Cite news|author=Mariolina Iossa|url=http://archiviostorico.corriere.it/1995/luglio/14/Castagna_saro_confessore_degli_italiani_co_0_9507143775.shtml|title=Castagna: sarò il confessore degli italiani|work=Corriere della Sera|location=Italy|date=1995-07-14|page=29|accessdate=25 January 2011|cid=|language=it}}</ref> and the summer primetime entertainment show ''Cuori e denari'', with [[Antonella Elia]] and [[Simona Ventura]].<ref name = MI />
In 1995/1996, Alberto Castagna presented the [[Canale 5]] afternoon show ''Casa Castagna'', directed by [[Gianni Boncompagni]]<ref>{{Cite news|author=Valerio Cappelli|url=http://archiviostorico.corriere.it/1995/settembre/17/Boncompagni_comanda_Casa_Castagna_co_0_9509179615.shtml|title=Boncompagni comanda in Casa Castagna|work=Corriere della Sera|location=Italy|date=1995-09-17|page=24|accessdate=25 January 2011|cid=|language=it}}</ref> In 1996 he was interrupted by "Ordine dei giornalisti" because of a violation of the rules about children on TV during an episode of ''Stranamore''. The year after has been radiated for repeating the same violation. It was reinstated in the "Ordine dei giornalisti" in 1999, after ricoursing<ref>{{Cite news|author=Valerio Cappelli|url=http://archiviostorico.corriere.it/1999/marzo/18/Alberto_Castagna_nuovo_giornalista_co_0_9903183340.shtml|title=Alberto Castagna di nuovo giornalista|work=Corriere della Sera|location=Italy|date=1999-03-18|page=24|accessdate=25 January 2011|cid=|language=it}}</ref>
In 1998 Alberto had a role as actor in the [[Retequattro]]'s fiction ''La villa dei misteri''. In the same year he suffered a double [[aneurysm]]; because of this he stayed in the hospital from July 18, 1998, to March 1999,<ref>{{Cite news|author=|url=http://archiviostorico.corriere.it/1999/marzo/14/Castagna_casa_dopo_otto_mesi_co_0_990314960.shtml|title=Castagna a casa dopo otto mesi|work=Corriere della Sera|location=Italy|date=1999-03-14|page=1|accessdate=25 January 2011|cid=|language=it}}</ref> attracting the attention of the Italian media because of his critical state of health. Despite everything, he had to undergo [[dialysis]] and wait for a kidney transplant.<ref>{{Cite news|author=Maria Volpe|url=http://archiviostorico.corriere.it/2001/aprile/28/Castagna_indignato_aspetto_trapianto_Mori_co_0_0104282165.shtml|title=Castagna indignato: aspetto un trapianto. La Mori: Adriano frainteso|work=Corriere della Sera|location=Italy|date=2001-04-28|page=33|accessdate=25 January 2011|cid=|language=it}}</ref> In 1999 he also released for [[Arnoldo Mondadori Editore]] the biographical book ''La mano sul cuore''.<ref>{{Cite news|author=Maria Volpe|url=http://archiviostorico.corriere.it/1999/maggio/05/Pucci_promise_eutanasia__co_0_9905056454.shtml|title=Pucci mi promise l'eutanasia|work=Corriere della Sera|location=Italy|date=1999-05-05|page=21|accessdate=25 January 2011|cid=|language=it}}</ref>
He came back on TV with his most important show, ''Stranamore'', in April 2001, aired by [[Canale 5]] on Sundays.<ref>{{Cite news|author=|url=http://archiviostorico.corriere.it/2001/aprile/24/Castagna_uguaglia_proprio_primato_con_co_0_010424109.shtml|title=Castagna uguaglia il proprio primato con oltre 10 milioni di telespettatori|work=Corriere della Sera|location=Italy|date=2001-04-23|page=37|accessdate=25 January 2011|cid=|language=it}}</ref> In the following years he continued presenting this show, having quite success and being moved to [[Retequattro]] in 2004. In that same year, Alberto hosted another primetime show for [[Retequattro]], ''Cosa non farei''.<ref>{{Cite news|author=|url=http://archiviostorico.corriere.it/2004/ottobre/23/Castagna_realizza_sogni_cambio_prove_co_9_041023086.shtml|title=Castagna realizza i sogni. In cambio di prove coraggiose|work=Corriere della Sera|location=Italy|date=2004-10-23|page=38|accessdate=25 January 2011|cid=|language=it}}</ref>
In February 2005, Alberto Castagna started presenting a new edition of ''Stranamore'', with [[Emanuela Folliero]], but it was never completed because of his death, which occurred on 1 March 2005 due to an [[internal bleeding]].<ref>{{Cite news|author=Renato Franco|url=http://archiviostorico.corriere.it/2005/marzo/03/Addio_Castagna_finisce_anche_show_co_9_050303092.shtml|title=Addio Castagna, finisce anche lo show Stranamore|work=Corriere della Sera|location=Italy|date=2005-03-03|page=41|accessdate=25 January 2011|cid=|language=it}}</ref> The news of his death was announced on live television from [[Paolo Bonolis]] during the 2005 edition of [[Festival di Sanremo]], the most important music festival in [[Italy]].<ref>{{Cite news|author=Maria Volpe|url=http://archiviostorico.corriere.it/2005/marzo/02/morte_Castagna_sgomento_Festival_co_8_050302001.shtml|title=La morte di Castagna, sgomento al Festival|work=Corriere della Sera|location=Italy|date=2005-02-03|page=39|accessdate=2011-01-25|cid=|language=it}}</ref>
In his life he was married with Maria Concetta "Pucci" Romano, from whom he had the daughter Carolina (1992), from 1994 to 1995.{{citation needed|date=February 2017}}
