{{Infobox Korean name| hangul= 삼| hanja= 參| mr= Sam| rr= Sam| }} '''Sam''' ({{Korean|삼|參}}) was one of the four members ([[No In]], [[Han Eum]], Sam and [[Wang Gyeop]]) who operated the government of [[Wiman Joseon]]. He was a [[chancellor]] of Nigye ([[Hangul]]:니계 [[Hanja]]:尼谿) and it was where he based himself for.<ref>{{Harvnb|Yukio Takeda|p=267}}</ref> He was an only one who did not have [[family name]] in those 4 members.<ref>{{Harvnb|Yukio Takeda|p=267}}</ref><ref>{{Harvnb|National Institute of Korean History||p=註 042}}</ref> In BC 109 to 108, when [[Han dynasty]] attacked Wiman Joseon, those three exiles from [[China]], No In, Han Eum and Wang Gyeop surrendered instantly while leaving the King of Wiman Joseon [[Ugeo]] and Sam was only one who resisted against Han dynasty among those members. However, in BC 108, Sam sent an assassin to Ugeo, killed him and urrendered to Han dynasty.<ref>{{Harvnb|Yukio Takeda|p=268}}</ref> After his surrender, he was nominated as a peerage of Hwae Cheong ([[Hangul]]:홰청 [[Hanja]]:澅清) by Han dynasty. 11 years later, he was arrested on suspicion of hiding the fugitive from Wiman Joseon and died of illness while he was in [[prison]].<ref>{{Harvnb|Yukio Takeda|p=269}}</ref>
==See also== *[[Han conquest of Gojoseon]]
